The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Krishnagar, May 14: Pinki Bhowmik, who was in Class IX, committed suicide this morning after being rebuked by her mother for being a laggard in school.

 The 16-year-olds results were published last week and she had failed in her class a second time. Police found her body hanging from a dupatta in her house at Chakdah, Nadia, about 60 km from Calcutta. They said both her parents were angry over the poor showing in class. Todays trouble started when Pinki went to a friends while her mother wanted her to help in some chores. When she returned, her mother was furious, an officer said. Her father Ramen, an affluent farmer, was not at home when she locked herself in her room.

 Calcutta: A Maruti car killed a young man on EM Bypass on Sunday night. Police said the driver, who also sustained serious injuries, hit a lamp post after knocking the youth down at Kadapara.

 Suri: Sheikh Alauddin, 14, a daily wager here, was run over by the rear wheels of a tractor he fell from near his village, 245 km from Calcutta.

 Behrampore: Murshidabad police chief N.K. Singh has ordered a probe into complaints that his men ransacked two houses and beat up residents during a raid on Saturday night. The police had gone to Mirdhapara in Raghunathgunj, 250 km from Calcutta, in search of some Congress supporters after a clash.




